**Render `SystemStatusZone`** — insert after the `</div>` that closes the message area container (the div with `className="relative min-h-0 flex-1"`) and before `<CelebrationOverlay>`. The exact insertion point is after the closing `</div>` at approximately line 333:

```typescript
      </div>

      <SystemStatusZone message={systemStatus} />

      <CelebrationOverlay
        celebration={celebrations.activeCelebration}
        onComplete={celebrations.clearCelebration}
      />
```

### 3. Export from barrel (if needed)

Check if `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/index.ts` exports UI components. If so, add `SystemStatusZone` to the exports. If the barrel only exports hooks/model, no change needed since `ChatPanel` imports it directly as a sibling.

## Testing

### 4. Create `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/__tests__/SystemStatusZone.test.tsx` (new file)

```typescript
/**
 * @vitest-environment jsdom
 */
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import '@testing-library/jest-dom';
import { SystemStatusZone } from '../SystemStatusZone';

describe('SystemStatusZone', () => {
  it('renders nothing when message is null', () => {
    const { container } = render(<SystemStatusZone message={null} />);
    // AnimatePresence renders nothing when children are falsy
    expect(container.textContent).toBe('');
  });

  it('renders message text when present', () => {
    render(<SystemStatusZone message="Compacting context..." />);
    expect(screen.getByText('Compacting context...')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it('renders with the expected styling classes', () => {
    render(<SystemStatusZone message="Test status" />);
    const text = screen.getByText('Test status');
    expect(text.tagName).toBe('SPAN');
    expect(text.className).toContain('text-xs');
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- `SystemStatusZone` renders nothing when `message` is null
- `SystemStatusZone` renders the message text with Info icon when `message` is a string
- Component uses `AnimatePresence` with opacity + height animation (0.2s duration)
- Uses `text-muted-foreground/60` for muted appearance
- Uses `text-xs` for small text size
- Component is rendered in ChatPanel between the message area and CelebrationOverlay
- `systemStatus` is properly threaded from `useChatSession` through ChatPanel to SystemStatusZone
- Tests pass: `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/__tests__/SystemStatusZone.test.tsx`
- No changes to existing components — compact_boundary messages render via the existing `UserMessageContent` component (which already handles `messageType: 'compaction'`)
- Full test suite passes: `pnpm test -- --run`
- TypeScript compiles: `pnpm typecheck`
